stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Ready : LoginContext LoginContext([String name])
    [*] --> Ready : LoginContext LoginContext([String name], [Subject subject])
    [*] --> Ready : LoginContext LoginContext([String name], [CallbackHandler callbackHandler])
    [*] --> Ready : LoginContext LoginContext([String name], [Subject subject], [CallbackHandler callbackHandler])
    [*] --> Ready : LoginContext LoginContext([String name], [Subject subject], [CallbackHandler callbackHandler], [Configuration config])

    Ready --> LoggedIn : void login()
    Ready --> Ready : Subject getSubject()

    LoggedIn --> LoggedIn : Subject getSubject()
    LoggedIn --> LoggedOut : void logout()

    LoggedOut --> LoggedOut : Subject getSubject()
    LoggedOut --> [*]

    note right of Ready
        login() throws LoginException on failure, state remains Ready.
        getSubject() returns null if authentication has not been attempted.
    end note

    note right of LoggedIn
        Subject is authenticated.
        getSubject() returns the authenticated Subject.
        A LoginContext should not authenticate more than one Subject.
    end note

    note right of LoggedOut
        Terminal state. logout() has been called.
        getSubject() may still return the Subject (if caller-specified or previously authenticated).
    end note
